	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105002935623135><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105002935623135>RE: Focus Effects</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105002935623135#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>142 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 10th 11:26 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The lower tier focus items work from levels 4 to 49. Soon as you get your pets, you can use them; IF you can get them. For the Vocerate spells, 51-60 you use the staves of elemental mastery. For the 61+ pets the only focus item that I know of is the Gloves of Dark Summoning from Vex Thal. That's according to Afterlife, and da spirits of da other worlds knows what dey be talkin' about.<br><br>/miss cleo off<br><br>Anyhoo, the lower level foci, the ones your talking about, they add stats. Fire gets the HP of air, air gets the HP of water, water gets the HP of earth, earth just gets a whole smegging ton of HP. You get the idea. The exact parsed info WAS on magecompendium.com but Ron has since removed it which sucks much.<br><br>There were a couple misunderstandings regarding there being a lower level limit on the foci taking effect, mainly for a while people thought that the foci only worked on the 34 to 49 pets.<br>However this has since been repeatedly disproven. Understandable mistake tho because at 34 the foci make yer pet frigging massive compared to the way it usually looks.<br><br>And yeah, once it's summoned it's summoned regardless if you still have the foci equipped. In otherwords, toss the foci on, summon up, and then toss that stuff back in your inventory.<br><br>Also, FYI hang on to the foci. Two of em are used for the epic and even after the epic still hang on to one. Much as we bitch and moan about having about 50 billion items with reclaim on em, not all of em are instant casts, so I'd reccomend hanging on to one for cannipetting till you get something better for the reclaim.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Legendary Mad Mage of Povar, 58th season, leader of Defiant Heroes, King of the karanas, Arch Nemesis of the Evil Squirrel Empire.<br><br><br>PS: for those of you reading this who don't know, cannipetting is the process of summoning and reclaiming pets over and over gaining mana each time, essentially giving one an unlimited mana pool. Don't really need to concern yourself with it till 49ish tho.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Apr 10 22:50:20 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
