<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=105099199490178></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105099199490178><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105099199490178>RE: Focus Effects</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105099199490178#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>142 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 22nd 2:51 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, the real burden from cannipetting isn't the price of malachite. 4 stacks costs only a few gold. The problem is lugging around 4 stacks of the damn stuff.<br><br>To make it easier you can use the summoned necklace, which randomly removes components from spells, or once ya hit 59 you could invest in the AA Elemental Pact, which eliminates the use of malachite once and for all.<br><br>And don't look on this as a replacement for KEI. Not till you get the support AA to make it really pracital. Look on it more as an aditional resource to be used with KEI should the need arise.<br><br>To make cannipetting most effective there are a few things you need. First off it helps big time to have your specialization set to conjuration. Second, a summoning efficency, mana reduction item, cast time reduction item, or any other kind of foci that improves summoning will also make a big difference.<br><br>Now, on AA. First off for pure reclaiming purposes, DO NOT TRAIN IMPROVED RECLAIM ENERGY.<br><br>Normal reclaim energy is based off the current hit points of a pet. In other words, if you canni a pet at full life you get more mana than you would if you canni a pet that's near dead. What improved reclaim energy does is make it a static value regardless of when you reclaim the pet. You'll gain mana sure. But not NEARLY as much as you would without it. Useful for chain casting pets, an extremely bad thing if you're looking to get some serious mana from cannipetting.<br><br>Now (and thanks to St. Jochan for the numbers) using the gloves of dark summoning and a SE4 item you could cast Rathe's Son (the best pet to canni assuming you don't have IRE) for a total of 240 mana and reclaim it for 550 mana giving you a net of 310 mana per 10 second (no cast time focus) cast. <br><br>Now, that boils down to a max of 186 mana per tic. Considering that c5 is a total of 18 mana per tic... I think you can see the way to go.<br><br>This is assuming a pretty damn high level of uberness, but it's possible to get decent numbers without all the drool worthy stuff.<br><br>One of the big things that you want to train AA wise is improved specialization and mana reduction stuffle. Beyond that pretty much anything you train along the lines of spec checks, or mana regen helps. Also, suspend minion is extremely helpful during this process, for reasons which should be obvious.<br><br>If you have already trained improve reclaim, you can regen mana on any pet you summon, right back down to level 4. Just not nearly as much mana as you would regen using the 49 earth 52 MS2 and rathe's son.<br><br>The thing with cannipetting is knowing when and how to use it. Once you get suspend minion you can put yer current pet away with full stats buffs and equip (on the second level of it) and bring it out when you're done cannipetting. Without suspend minion though, which takes a pretty high level to even start learning, you need to put a bit more thought into when to drop your pet and start the cani cycle. A good way to look at it is medding without sitting down and no pet.<br><br>This is a tool that if used properly can redefine the role of a mage. Just be careful with it. Even with this much mana regen, a mage with no pet can quickly lose the DPS that makes us useful in the first place.<br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br><br>PS: Cannipetting is something that to my knowledge really only starts working with the 49 earth pet. There may be lower level pets that you can gain mana reclaiming, but if there are it's not common knowledge. Anyone parsed it to find out?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr 22 02:39:01 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
