	   <a name=104989762514336></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104989762514336><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104989762514336>RE: AoE</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104989762514336#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=191870><span id= >Sirulus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>27 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 9th 10:50 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well from seeing your post, I will assume that you are on a PvP server or one that allows your teammates to take dmg from your spells. With that in mind I will try to help you out. <br><br>Typically the purpose is for non PvP or servers that are not set for your group to take dmg from your spells. In group situations however I would recommend not to use them. I however use them heavily in the Planes of Power if we pull clean because I am on a server where my spells do not affect my group (Pulling clean is when we get singles or we seperate the mobs far enough apart during the mezzing of adds).<br><br>The way I will approach your question is from my viewpoint and is in no way the only way to do it so if others have views, feel free to add them. I generally use...okay I ALWAYS use my earth pet to solo as he can root and allow me to nuke effetively. That in mind I let him do at least 80% of the damage before I lay on the nukes. I find that I can nuke up to 5 times in a row, (Chain), before I take agro from my pet. Then I simply dodge around till his root holds again. I use rain when I pull the mob to an area that the pet can tank him and not pick up adds from my AE (Dungeons are not good ideas as there is a downstairs and upstairs and believe it or not sometimes mobs upstairs get hit by the AE unless they fixed this. So far PoJ is the only place I have found that there was no agro from below...)<br><br>Rain IMHO is the most mana efficient way to nuke to an extent. You get 3 nukes in one cast (Waves) and can therefore save mana and down time. I say to an extent because some times it may be resisted and also the mob will move too fast to get hit by the full blast of an AE. Magicians are one of the more mana efficient of the casting classes as we have pets that do a good deal of damage and the Earth pet roots so it saves us the mana needed for that. I can sorta see AE nukes working in a group if you hotkey messages to warn the tanks/melee to back up while you AE. An example of this would be if you put up an Earth pet and his root holds you can type, &quot;AE Rain of Lava incoming in 20 seconds&quot; would provide them time to back off and out of range. I use a message similar to this and have my hotkey set up as such:<br><br>Hotkey Label - Rain<br>Line 1 of hotkey reads:<br>/g By Mithanel Marr, rain your lava unto %t (This is an AoE spell so warn me now if I need to cancel casting)<br>Line 2 of hotkey reads:<br>/pause 25<br>Line 3 of hotkey reads:<br>/cast 6<br>Line 4 of hotkey reads:<br>/pause 15<br>Line 5 of hotkey reads:<br>/g And by Marr, so it rains!!!<br><br>Now this may be a bit wordy in a hotkey but I find that it gets their attention and they will warn you if you should not cast it. I have never been warned but I still use it as sometimes in PoD if you fight at LC you realize that sometimes adds pop and you cannot see where they are from your vantage point and in your eagerness to help out you could cause trouble. (My rain spell does 1890 dmg if it is not resisted and therefore VERY mana efficient IMHO and helpful.)<br><br>You may have to work on the /pause XX command before you find the right timing but that is what I use for my own hotkeys. I do not play on servers where my groupmates take dmg from my nukes so I have not needed to test it out and therefore this is just a theory but post me back and let me know how it works. I hope it works as it will find you with more mana and therefore less in need for med time.<br><br>Also I am available to help you as much as a 58th level Mage can so feel free to post again.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;9 10:14:27 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Boka Slyfox <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=658921" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=658921</a><br>38 Rogue ~ Tunare Server<br>/ooc 38 Rogue looking for a Guild. I dont do raids, dont do groups...I like to steal and ninja loot PST</td></tr>
