	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104833734310006><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104833734310006>RE: what is the best pet</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=104833734310006#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>142 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 22nd 8:24 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kk... here's the rundown.<br><br>Water: good damage output, fast regen, high poison resist. Good group pet, can get risky in solo situations occasionally. Honestly this is probably the pet I used the least leveling up, but once ya get to 54+ the backstab that the pet develops makes it ideal for a lot of group situations. Also heard on occasion that the 61+ version of this pet can assassinate for 32k damage on lower level mobs. Not sure on that yet tho.<br><br>Air: Also good damage output, high dodge, lot of damage avoidance, casts a nice stun, which makes it ideal for any sort of casting mob, or damage mitigation in groups where you're with a tank who can't take too much of a beating. Use yer highest malise type spell first to increase effectiveness. The 53+ ones develop damage added to the stun.<br><br>Fire: High attack, great damage shield, extremely high fire resist which makes it good for mobs with nasty fire AoEs such as naggy, faydawer, and Rak'Ashir in CoM. A pretty good pet to use solo, but yer gonna end up healing it lots due to the low HP. 52 version sucks much, however there MAY be ways to improve it. Just pretty sure I've seen the 52 one cast burst of flame. Lots. I have heard however that the 58 and up ones are considerably better. Still 2 yellows or so away from there tho so can't verify it personally yet. Unlike the other pets the 52+ fire ones have a mana bar rather than using their elemental attack as a proc, so they may get a benifit from using the summoned casting foci. Have yet to test this though do to a sever attack of lazyness.<br><br>Earth: earth pets are one of my favorites. They're good for soloing because they can take one heck of a beating. Particularly if you buff them with a DS and give them summoned armor. However they do have their limits, and if you use them in a group with rogues, rangers, druids, shammies, wizzies, or chanties, you may get a smack upside the head. Far as I can tell the earth pet root overwrites PC roots, which can throw off timing. Rangers can't get full damage using arrows on mobs that are rooted, and rogues bitch because with an earth pet a rooted mob will attack whoever is closest regardless of the hate list. Generally not a good pet to use in groups. There are exceptions, but they're few and far between.<br><br>The monster summons are mostly for looks. Rage of zomm can be mighty handy in a raid situation if used properly and ya haven't anything better. and Dzyil's deafining decoy can be neat in certain situations where you want it to get all the aggro, but those don't crop up too often.<br><br><br>That's the basic rundown. In groups fire, water, or air if yer up against casters, solo earth with a DS or fire. or water. or air.<br><br>Oh hell you know what they all do. Just use your own judgement. In the end it's all pretty well balanced. heh.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar, Leader of Defiant Heroes[tm] and arch nemesis of the evil squirrel empire.<br><br>&quot;There but for the grace of a Hate stick and an air crown, go I.&quot; -Fae<br><br><br><br>(Edit) PS: pretty sure pets get dual wield at 24. been a while tho. As for race, well, being a high elf has worked for me for 57 levels. Race these days is really pretty much for looks tho. By the time you get higher in levels it really ceases to matter. High elves and gnomes appear to be the two really popular races for mages tho. But that may just be povar.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Mar 31 10:58:07 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
