	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105054272050735><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105054272050735>RE: information</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=105054272050735#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=195657><span id=Scholar>Yanari</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>55 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 16th 9:25 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Unlike some other classes, magicians must create some of their own spells.<br><br>Put at least 1 training point (more if you can) into research at level 16.&nbsp;&nbsp;At your guild hall, purchase an &quot;elemental grimoire&quot;.  This book is actually the container in which you combine your research components.  I looked up my spell recipes at castersrealm.com instead of buying books at my guild hall.  It was just more convenient for me.  Here's one of the level 16 spell recipes:<br><br>Spell, Minor Summoning Water Elemental.  <br>Requires: Summon Water Elemental (level 12 water pet spell), Shark Skin, Words of Tyranny.<br><br>Place these components into your elemental grimoire, cross your fingers and hit the &quot;combine&quot; button.  If you fail, do it again.  That's really all there is to it.<br>&nbsp;<br>Merry meet, merry part, and merry meet again.<br><br>Yanari, Witch of Felwithe</td></tr>
