	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good info as always Yanari, one little addendum. Research is a royal pain in the ass. It used to be totally and utterly pointless, because in order to max it you either had to spend ages farming greens for skill parts, or spend a fortune to buy skill points from a trainer<br><br>However with the edition of LoY it might be worth investing in because you can get some hard to find or expensive spells a LOT cheaper. Like burnout 4 which I spent quite a long time trying to find for under 6kish, then with LoY managed to research for a total of 800pp. Made a couple copies that sold pretty fast too, which more than made up the 4kish I spend to get the last 50 points or so. That and we're able to research some wis caster spells now as well.<br><br>Regardless, It's getting to the point where it's worth maxing research, or at the least making friends with someone who has.<br><br>That said, buy your skill points. It gets expensive, but much less of a headache in the long run.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar, 210 skill mage researcher for hire.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Apr 19 17:39:43 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
